      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TIMELESS GRACIE (1) carved over from wide out and boxed on strongly to finish half a length away in second (19.73) behind SHIMA SAND at this track. Has performed well from this box with a win and three minor placings to her name from five starts. Likely to be in the finish again. SCOOBY DANGER (2) was a last-start winner from the inside at Launceston over 515m (30.05), scoring by 3.5 lengths. Hard to beat again here. SHIMA SAND (4) is a sprinter who thrives over these shorter races. Was too tough when scoring last time over 340m at this track in a Grade 5 (19.70). Strike rate this course and distance strong having won two of three tries. Has won two of four starts from this draw. One of the leading chances again.",
